WiseTech Global is a world-leading software company building software for the global logistics industry. We are united in our mission to create breakthrough products that enable and empower those who own and operate the supply chains of the world. More than 18,000 logistics organizations use our software solutions, including 24 of the top 25 global freight forwarders and 41 of the top 50 global third-party logistics providers.

We’re an engineer-led company focusing on building secure, scalable products. Therefore, data analytics is critical to the function of the international supply chain.

As a Sydney or Melbourne-based data analyst, you will be responsible for designing and building data models to enhance analytics and performance reporting and optimizing data flow and collection for cross-functional teams.

About the role:

By joining the team, you will be responsible for analyzing available data sources and giving recommendations on data integration and processing, building data models for predictive and prescriptive analytics, investigating, and interpreting data, and building prototypes for analytics reports.

If you are self-directed and are comfortable supporting the data needs of the business, systems, and products - this role is for you!

Key responsibilities:
• Communicating with stakeholders to understand and write technical and business requirements for use cases.
• Statistical analysis of data in multiple data sources, creating data profiles.
• Identifying and implementing data quality control processes that prompt correction in the source systems where required.
• Developing data models, flows, datasets, and views that are efficient and meaningful representations of data.
• Designing reporting solutions and building prototypes.
• Communicating and coordinating effectively with data owners, product people, and other stakeholders to ensure models and results are well understood and incorporated into their business processes.
• Developing and implementing testing plans for data transformations, maintaining data definition and technical documentation.
• Driving awareness and providing expertise on the use of analytics tools and concepts, providing training and effectively communicating with multiple stakeholders.
• Analysing existing data governance and privacy requirements and identifying areas for improvement.

To be successful in this role, you will have:
• 2-6 years of commercial experience in a similar role
• Strong understanding of business analysis methodologies and techniques, including requirements gathering, process modelling, and documentation
• Experience of working with notebooks
• Deep understanding of databases
• Experience in Data Design work
• Expertise in Microsoft BI stack (MS SQL, SSIS, SSAS, Power BI, OLAP)
• Experience working with SQL and visualization tools like Tableau or Power BI,
• Basic Python skills
• Experience with Statistical Modelling
• Practical knowledge of data warehousing concepts
• Knowledge of Data Governance concepts, industry best practices, and principles
• Solid SQL experience, authoring complex queries and DDL, working with execution plans
• Basic knowledge of machine learning (E.g. Spark ML or Python ML)

Business & Data Requirements
• Engage stakeholders to establish a common understanding of the business and data needs
• Identify and correctly translate business needs into business requirements and data solution requirements

Intuit HQ is based in Mountain View California where we have been in operations since 1983. We are proud to share that Intuit has consistently appeared in Fortune’s top 50 Best companies to work for over the last 5 years. We believe in the power of the individual. The power to do more. To make more. To be more.

The Data Analytics team is looking for a talented Staff Data Analyst to drive GTM initiatives across the Australian & Rest of World businesses. You should be a driven fast learner and high achiever with a passion to continuously learn, grow and deliver well in a high performance and flexible hybrid working environment characterized by speed, collaboration, creativity and fun.

As a Staff Analyst, you will work closely with our GTM Teams to develop insights, lead experimentation, and drive key business results. You will take complex concepts and communicate them to both technical and non-technical leaders in order to effect change for our customers. You will be an instrumental leader in shaping the strategy, working across Marketing, Sales, Intuit AI and Data Engineering to drive an integrated plan to grow and scale our Advisor business.

Responsibilities

This role is a critical partner, leading data and analytics for complex strategic businessinitiatives.

• You will use your business domain knowledge in combination with data and analytics to lead projects, including market/category insights, experiment design, creating dashboards, measuring business results, and analysing customer behaviour.

• Proven experience as a data analyst or in a similar role, with excellent data interpretation.
• Knowledge of the real estate industry is a bonus, with the ability to understand industry-specific trends and concepts.
• Strong team player with the ability to collaborate effectively and contribute to a positive work
• environment.

About the role:

Data analytics in the energy and climate space is growing at an incredible rate. Blunomy provides data-based solutions to support the energy industry, financial institutions and supply chains through their digitisation, decentralisation and decarbonisation transitions. Our tools support improved energy market operability, automation and planning. We are also developing digital solutions that better measure impact and transition speed, to help decarbonise financial resources.

We are looking for someone who is passionate about energy, climate change and data analytics to do-well-and-do-good by delivering data science products to crack transition challenges. As a Manager, you will be responsible for:
• Identify and pursue new business opportunities for the data science team
• Managing the end-to-end delivery of the project
• Engaging and communicating with the client
• Anticipating and managing project risks, timelines, and budget
• Managing and leading analysts and senior analysts

In this setting, you will be exposed to the diversity of current energy challenges, leveraging your data and analytical skills to address them. We are always growing the products we deliver but over the last 12 months we have delivered:
• Load forecasting: model and predict the evolution of the load on the electrical network. Use machine learning, data analytics and a fair amount of software development to forecast long-term energy consumption, daily energy profiles and Distributed Energy Resources (Electric Vehicles, Battery, Solar PV).
• PV connections approval tool: dynamically model the energy network bringing together power flow modelling and machine learning to determine the PV hosting capacity of the local area. Used in production to approve hundreds of PV connection requests a day.
• Vegetation management using LiDAR: collect three‑dimensional images of the local network gathered by drone or helicopter. Use machine learning and geometric models to detect and manage vegetation near powerlines.
• Bushfire risk modelling: model and compute the network‑related bushfire risk based on fault ignition likelihood. Calculate the consequences of bushfires such as property damage or agricultural loss.
• Low-Voltage network mapping: identify errors within the current mapping of the low-voltage network, especially targeting customers whom connection to the network has not been properly recorded. This was performed using outlier detection with out-of-bag predictors.

Depending on the objectives, projects will entail tasks of varying nature. Your first focus will be on projects requiring data analytics capabilities.
